# CLI Usage

The CLI tool [bin/cli.mjs](mdc:bin/cli.mjs) provides two main commands:

## 1. Configuration Setup (`config`)
```bash
npx eslint-config-ts-prefixer config
```
This command:
- Creates `.eslintrc.cjs`, `.eslintignore`, `.prettierrc`, and `.prettierignore` files
- Adds `lint` and `lint:fix` scripts to your package.json
- Updates your tsconfig.json to include necessary files for TypeScript ESLint parsing

## 2. Barebone Installation (`barebone`)
```bash
npx eslint-config-ts-prefixer barebone
```
This command:
- Copies the full ESLint configuration directly to your project as `.eslintrc.cjs`
- Creates all other configuration files
- Adds `lint` and `lint:fix` scripts to your package.json
- Updates your tsconfig.json as needed

The barebone approach lets you customize rules while the standard install uses the package as an extension.
